FYI: prompt_toolkit 1.0.4 has been released, which contains these fixes.

@rgom: regarding the first screenshot and the colors of the comment: I think IPython could pick a slightly different colorscheme when running on Windows. But also keep in mind that Windows consoles only have 16 colors, which are configurable. IPython does not have that much control of which actual colors the user assigns to these 16 colors.

@takluyver, not sure if we could use some slightly different colors for Windows. For ptpython, I have hardcoded a color scheme that seems to work well on Windows: https://github.com/jonathanslenders/ptpython/blob/master/ptpython/style.py#L52
